OL,3,CNuclear fusion reactor celebrates 40
OL,4,Cyears of pioneering scientific finds
OL,6,FResearchers generated 69 megajoules of
OL,7,Fenergy over five seconds from a mere
OL,8,F0.2 milligrams of fuel in the final
OL,9,Ffusion experiment in December 2023.
OL,11,FThe burst of energy, equivalent to
OL,12,F16.5kg of TNT, was described as a
OL,13,F"fitting swansong" for the project,
OL,14,Fwhich has pioneered technology for
OL,15,Ffuture commercial fusion reactors
OL,16,Fsince it began operating in 1983.
OL,18,FIt beat the previous record of 59
OL,19,Fmegajoules of heat, set by the same
OL,20,Ffacility in 2022.
